The paper deals with the complexity of factoring polynomials, which is a problem in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of combinatorial objects called m-schemes suggests a connection to discrete mathematics and combinatorics (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of information theory (cs.IT) in the analysis of the algorithm. The mention of the generalized Riemann Hypothesis (GRH) suggests a connection to cryptography (cs.CR) and number theory (cs.NT).
